Sounds to me, after reading the reactions on this thread, that Hollywood has overplayed its hand on drugs at the front line. Big Time. So did &quot;our&quot; beloved media. I think of the movie Platoon, and the imfamous drug scene (&quot;the worm has definately turned on you pal...) and I am not surprised.  <br><br>
I know of a story that goes like this: A guy in the anti-war culture (i.e. Time Magazine's &quot;hippy&quot; thing) would take Lindy ink pens (long and cheap ball points), cut down the ink cartridge, and fill them with LSD tabs (usually orange sunshine or Oswley barrels). Put the pen cap back on and mail a box full of purple ink to his pal in Nam.  Got to him easy. The pal in the bush would load up anything that would hold Nam Weed and ship it back to the States.  The common bitch was that good acid was hard to get in Nam, but all the weed, etc. was easy.  God, the idea of tripping on LSD in Viet Nam is so oxymoronish, so horrible, that I want to have a flashback and puke, at the same time. I can not believe that anyone would be so suicidal, but too many stories must have a basis in fact somewhere.<br><br>
What about the body bags and even bodies being stuffed with drugs and flown back to the USA?  This was a common theme in all the T.V. News and Tabloid Press on and off at least monthly during the war.  There were even those self-righteous &quot;leaders&quot; who wanted the war ended JUST to stop the flow of drugs back to the motherland.<br><br>
A close friend of mine did his tour in Cam Ran (sp?) Bay doing longshore and warehouse stuff. Said he was stoned everyday due to the heat and boredom, and never fired a shot.  I guess he doesn't know how lucky he was.<br><br>
A personal aside: While I was swimming in the thick of the civilian drug thing, I am thankful now that (1) the brain damage is minimal...duh, what was I saying...(2) I still believe that LSD flashbacks are bullshit, and only happen to those with &quot;weak&quot; minds...duh what was that elephant on my ceiling saying to me....and (3) I am thankful to all Gods both big and small, that both of my kids are D.A.R.E., Scared Straight, Just Say No to Drugs, Drug Abuse is Life Abuse, and &quot;straight edgers&quot;.  Hard to say no to a second set of ear piercing when they don't do booze or drugs.  Damn, what a role model for the old man to fail to keep up with.<br><br>
